This is a demo of the gaze-contingent setup used in the study of the dynamics of the functional field of view. 

The design was manipulated via stimuli inversion (*upright vs inverted*) combined with three gaze-contingent aperture sizes (*6°, 12° & 18°*).
This study was a part of my PhD thesis. 

The original publication can be read [here](https://doi.org/https://doi.org/10.1145/3655597/)
